---
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Starboard | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Starboard</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Starboard is a New Zealand-based maritime intelligence platform that helps
      government agencies, security teams, and researchers monitor vessel activity
      in real-time to spot patterns and take action when it matters most.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Built alongside government users across New Zealand, Australia, and the
      Pacific, the platform processes over 4,000 vessel positions per second,
      enabling informed decisions without waiting for outdated reports.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I partnered with Starboard's Chief of Product and Chief of Marketing
      to improve their web experience as they expanded globally. Prospects were
      struggling to find relevant information about how the platform fit their workflows.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Website Redesign</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Government agencies and maritime organizations struggled to find what they needed
      on Starboard's outdated website. Researchers couldn't locate illegal fishing case studies,
      border security teams couldn't find vessel tracking capabilities, and conservation officers
      couldn't discover real-time alert tools for their missions.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Working with Sales and Customer Success, I conducted a content audit
      to understand exactly what different users were trying to accomplish.
      What I discovered was that officials needed to see how Starboard solved problems
      similar to theirs before exploring technical details.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-one.png"
      alt="Homepage design showcasing maritime surveillance expertise and global reach."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-two.png"
      alt="Solutions page highlighting real-time vessel tracking and analytics capabilities."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I designed and built over 20 pages on Webflow while migrating 100+
      existing articles. Each page was positioned for a different use case, ensuring they could
      quickly find relevant case studies and technical documentation.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      The redesign was completed in 3 months, delivering clearer product positioning, helping prospects move from
      interest to qualified conversations faster.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-three.png"
      alt="Resource center design organizing maritime intelligence insights and case studies."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/starboard-website-four.png"
      alt="About page emphasizing team expertise and company mission in ocean protection."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
</Layout>
